This is equivalent to: `Fin (n - 1 + 1) = Fin n`. So `Fin (n - 1 + 1)` is rewritten to `Fin n`.
Then `congr_arg Fin ...` is applying `Fin` to both sides of the equality. This seems redundant.

The simpler form is just using the range `0..Fin.last n`. This range has length `n`, which is the size of `Fin n`. This is the standard way to define a uniform distribution over `Fin n`.

