   ```tactics
   $[0..Fin.last n]
   ```
   This uses the standard library's definition of `Fin.last` which gives the maximum value in `Fin n`, i.e., `n - 1`. The range `0..Fin.last n` will therefore be `0, 1, ..., n-1`, which has length `n`. This is the standard way to define a uniform distribution over `Fin n`.

